HEADWORD: Ibero-mesornis
<hw>Ibero-mesornis</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sparrow-sized fossil bird
of the Lower Cretaceous having a strutlike pectoral bone and vestigial
tail; found in Spain; considered possibly the third most primitive of
all birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

